        <h3>6. Verify Citations and Referencing Styles</h3>

        <p>Accurate referencing is critical to maintaining 
        academic integrity. Check whether your essay strictly 
        adheres to your assigned guide such as APA format, 
        Harvard format, MLA, or Chicago style. Ensure every 
        paraphrased idea or direct quote has a corresponding 
        in-text citation. Utilizing professional 
        <a href="https://thesisarcpro.github.io/contact">research paper writing</a> 
        support can help ensure your references are aligned with 
        current institutional guidelines.</p>

        <h3>7. Perform a Spelling, Punctuation, and Typos 
        Check</h3>

        <p>Do not rely solely on automated spellcheckers as they 
        often miss context-specific errors such as confusing 
        their, there, and they're, or effect and affect. Read 
        your paper slowly word by word. Check consistency in 
        spelling conventions throughout the document — British 
        English or American English.</p>

        <h3>8. Check Word Count and Prompt Requirements</h3>

        <p>Compare your current word count against the assignment 
        prompt. Remember to verify whether your title page, 
        footnotes, and bibliography are included in or excluded 
        from the official limit. Re-read the assignment rubric 
        to ensure you have answered every part of the question.</p>

        <h3>9. Execute a Thorough Plagiarism Check</h3>

        <p>Ensure that any ideas taken from external sources are 
        written entirely in your own words and properly credited. 
        Double-check that all direct quotes are enclosed in 
        quotation marks. Consider running your paper through a 
        reliable academic scanning tool before submitting to your 
        university's submission portal.</p>

        <h3>10. Final Formatting and Visual Presentation</h3>

        <p>Check that your margins, line spacing, and font size 
        conform to your department's stylesheet. Ensure page 
        numbers are correctly placed and your title page is 
        formatted correctly. If you are preparing a major 
        milestone paper, seeking specialist 
        <a href="https://thesisarcpro.github.io/contact">thesis and dissertation help</a> 
        can help verify that your formatting meets university 
        guidelines.</p>

        <h2>What to Look for When Editing an Essay: Editing 
        vs. Revising</h2>

        <p>Many students use the terms revising and editing 
        interchangeably, but they refer to different stages 
        of the writing cycle.</p>

        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Stage</th>
              <th>Focus Area</th>
              <th>Key Questions</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Revising</td>
              <td>Logical structure, argument strength, overall 
