              <td>Are there spelling errors? Are my citations 
              correct?</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>What to check before submitting an essay?</h3>
        <p>Before submitting an essay, check that your thesis 
        statement is clear, your body paragraphs are logically 
        structured with strong topic sentences, and your 
        arguments transition smoothly. Verify that all sources 
        are cited correctly, check your final word count, and 
        proofread carefully for spelling and punctuation errors.</p>

        <h3>What is an editing checklist?</h3>
        <p>An editing checklist is a systematic guide used by 
        writers to review and polish their drafts. It helps 
        ensure that both high-level elements such as logical 
        arguments and structure and low-level details such as 
        grammar, spelling, and citation formatting are thoroughly 
        evaluated before final submission.</p>

        <h3>What to look for when editing an essay?</h3>
        <p>When editing an essay, look for clarity of expression, 
        appropriate academic tone, proper sentence variation, 
        coherent transitions between paragraphs, and correct 
        word choices. Ensure that your paragraphs focus on a 
        single main idea and support your overall thesis 
        statement.</p>

        <h3>What is the checklist for revising?</h3>
        <p>The checklist for revising includes: verifying that 
        the central thesis is clear and arguable, ensuring each 
        paragraph supports the main thesis, checking the logical 
        flow and transition of arguments, adding or clarifying 
        evidence where arguments feel weak, and removing 
        redundant or irrelevant information.</p>

